{# Exchange compliance records request (v0.14.11).

   Sent directly from the operator's compliance team to the CEX's
   compliance team — NOT a court-issued subpoena. This is the
   "Exhibit C" pattern: operator-direct records request citing
   documented theft evidence, requesting (1) KYC on the user who
   controlled the deposit address, (2) onward transfer / off-ramp
   records, (3) hold on remaining funds if applicable.

   Exchanges respond to these directly when accompanied by
   appropriate evidence + LE coordination. For cases that need
   formal compelled disclosure, the AUSA grand-jury subpoena
   template (subpoena_request.html.j2) is the right path.

   Required Jinja context:
     - case_id, generated_at (UTC ISO)
     - victim: dict with name, jurisdiction
     - exchange: dict with name, legal_name, compliance_email,
       address, registered_agent (optional)
     - flows: list of OnwardCEXFlow-shaped dicts:
       - upstream_address, cex_address, token_symbol,
         flow_usd_value (formatted "$X,XXX.XX"), transfer_count,
         first_flow_at, last_flow_at, tx_hashes (list),
         upstream_explorer_url, cex_explorer_url
     - investigator: dict with name, organization, email
     - le_engaged: bool (was law enforcement engaged for this case?)
     - le_reference: optional IC3 / FBI case ID
#}<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Exchange Records Request — Case {{ case_id }}</title>
{% include "_styles.html.j2" %}
</head>
<body>

<section class="cover">
  <div class="cover-letterhead">
    <div class="cover-wordmark">
      Recupero
      <span class="tagline">Investigation Services</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-letterhead-right">
      <div class="confidential">Strictly Private &amp; Confidential</div>
      <div class="date">{{ generated_at }} UTC</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="cover-title-block">
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">Exchange Compliance Records Request</div>
    <h1>{{ exchange.name }}<br/>Records Request</h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">
      On-chain tracing establishes that funds stolen from {{ victim.name }}
      were forwarded from identified upstream addresses to
      {{ flows|length }} deposit address(es) under
      {{ exchange.name }}'s custody. We respectfully request your
      compliance team's cooperation in identifying the controlling
      customer(s) and producing the records described below.
    </p>
    <div class="cover-rule"></div>
  </div>

  <dl class="cover-meta">
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Addressed To</dt>
      <dd>{{ exchange.legal_name or exchange.name }}<span class="secondary">Compliance &amp; AML Team<br/>{{ exchange.compliance_email }}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Prepared By</dt>
      <dd>{{ investigator.name }}<span class="secondary">{{ investigator.organization }}<br/>on behalf of {{ victim.name }}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Case Number</dt>
      <dd>{{ case_id }}</dd>
    </div>
    {% if le_reference %}
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>LE Reference</dt>
      <dd class="mono">{{ le_reference }}</dd>
    </div>
    {% endif %}
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Total Flow Value</dt>
      <dd>{{ total_flow_usd }}<span class="secondary">across {{ flows|length }} flow(s)</span></dd>
    </div>
  </dl>
</section>

<section class="content">

<h2>1. Nature of the Underlying Matter</h2>
<p>
On {{ incident_date }}, {{ victim.name }} ({{ victim.jurisdiction }})
reported the unauthorized appropriation of digital assets from
{{ victim.name|default("a Recupero client") }}'s self-custodied
wallet. The reported loss is approximately {{ total_loss_usd }}.
{% if le_engaged %}
Law enforcement has been engaged in this matter
{% if le_reference %}
under reference {{ le_reference }}.
{% else %}
and is actively investigating.
{% endif %}
{% else %}
Engagement with law enforcement is pending the outcome of the
investigative steps described in this request.
{% endif %}
</p>

<h2>2. On-Chain Evidence of {{ exchange.name }} Receipt</h2>
<p>
Independent on-chain analysis of the stolen-fund flow identified
that the upstream addresses listed below — themselves identified
as recipients of the misappropriated assets — subsequently
forwarded {{ token_summary }} to deposit addresses under
{{ exchange.name }}'s custody. The flows are summarized in the
table that follows; each transaction is independently verifiable
on the public blockchain.
</p>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Upstream (sender)</th>
      <th>{{ exchange.name }} deposit (receiver)</th>
      <th>Token</th>
      <th class="amount">Total USD</th>
      <th>Transfers</th>
      <th>Period</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {% for flow in flows %}
    <tr>
      {# v0.32.1 (Jacob cross-cutting audit §3.1): canonical short_address filter. #}
      <td class="mono">{% if flow.upstream_explorer_url %}<a href="{{ flow.upstream_explorer_url|safe_url }}">{{ flow.upstream_address | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=6) }}</a>{% else %}<span>{{ flow.upstream_address | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=6) }}</span>{% endif %}</td>
      <td class="mono">{% if flow.cex_explorer_url %}<a href="{{ flow.cex_explorer_url|safe_url }}">{{ flow.cex_address | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=6) }}</a>{% else %}<span>{{ flow.cex_address | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=6) }}</span>{% endif %}</td>
      <td>{{ flow.token_symbol }}</td>
      <td class="amount mono">{{ flow.flow_usd_value }}</td>
      <td class="amount mono">{{ flow.transfer_count }}</td>
      <td>
        {# v0.16.2 (audit fix #4): guard against None — the worker's
           defensive serializer writes null when Transfer.block_time
           is missing. Pre-fix the [:10] slice raised AttributeError
           and crashed the whole render. #}
        {% if flow.first_flow_at %}
          {{ flow.first_flow_at[:10] }}
          {% if flow.last_flow_at and flow.last_flow_at[:10] != flow.first_flow_at[:10] %}
            – {{ flow.last_flow_at[:10] }}
          {% endif %}
        {% else %}—{% endif %}
      </td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>3. Transaction Hashes (for Verification)</h2>
<p>The flows above comprise the following on-chain transactions. Each
hash is reproducible against any Ethereum mainnet node or block
explorer:</p>
<ul style="font-family: ui-monospace, 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.85em;">
{% for flow in flows %}
{% for tx in flow.tx_hashes %}
  <li>{{ tx }}<span class="secondary"> · {{ flow.upstream_address | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=6) }} → {{ flow.cex_address | short_address(prefix=10, suffix=6) }} · {{ flow.token_symbol }}</span></li>
{% endfor %}
{% endfor %}
</ul>

<h2>4. Records Requested</h2>
<p>
For each {{ exchange.name }}-controlled deposit address listed in
section 2, we respectfully request that your compliance team
produce the following records:
</p>
<ol>
  <li>
    <strong>Customer identification.</strong> The identity of the
    customer associated with the deposit address (full legal name,
    date of birth, residence and mailing address, and government-
    issued identification on file). This may be produced under
    your internal compliance-cooperation framework or, where
    required, under formal compelled-disclosure process via the
    contact listed in section 6.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Deposit confirmation.</strong> Confirmation that the
    {{ token_summary }} flow into the deposit address was credited
    to the associated customer account, the value as recorded on
    your platform, and the post-deposit balance available for
    redemption or onward transfer.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Onward activity.</strong> All on-platform transfers,
    conversions, and withdrawal events involving the deposited
    {{ token_summary }} or its converted form, with the
    destination address(es) for any on-chain withdrawal.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Hold action.</strong> To the extent the funds remain
    on the platform under the associated customer account, please
    place a precautionary hold pending engagement with law
    enforcement representatives identified in section 6.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Compliance flags.</strong> Any internal risk-rating,
    KYT, or fraud-monitoring annotations your team has placed on
    the addresses or associated customer accounts.
  </li>
</ol>

<h2>5. Use and Confidentiality of Response</h2>
<p>
Any information produced in response to this request will be used
exclusively for the purpose of investigating and remediating the
underlying theft. Distribution of customer-identifying records
will be limited to Recupero's investigative counsel and engaged
law enforcement agencies. Where {{ exchange.name }}'s policy
requires formal compelled disclosure (subpoena, court order,
MLAT), please notify the contact in section 6 and we will
coordinate the appropriate process via the engaged AUSA's office.
</p>

<h2>6. Point of Contact</h2>
<p>
<strong>Investigative counsel:</strong><br/>
{{ investigator.name }}<br/>
{{ investigator.organization }}<br/>
{{ investigator.email }}
</p>
{% if le_engaged %}
<p>
<strong>Engaged law enforcement:</strong><br/>
{% if le_reference %}
Reference {{ le_reference }} (point of contact available upon request
via the investigative counsel above)
{% else %}
[LE coordinator available upon request via the investigative
counsel above]
{% endif %}
</p>
{% endif %}

<h2>7. Response Window</h2>
<p>
We respectfully request acknowledgement of receipt within five (5)
business days, and production of the records described above
within fifteen (15) business days where compliance-cooperation
process applies, or notice of the formal-process requirement
within the same window.
</p>

</section>

</body>
</html>
